This paper discusses the technological improvements and economic analysis of mobile network providers, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The study also considers the environmental impacts of LTE, which could be categorized under computer and society (cs.CE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The techno-economic analysis conducted in the study involves the use of primary researched tariff data, which could be categorized under information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study also considers the security implications of LTE, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
